Last updated: June 3, 2024

This Privacy Policy outlines the practices of our demo app regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of personal information when you use our services. By using our demo app, you agree to the collection and use of information as described in this policy.

1. **Information Collection and Use**

    a. **Facebook Login**: When you choose to log in to our app using Facebook, we may collect your basic profile information such as your name, email address, and profile picture. We may also collect additional information based on your Facebook privacy settings.

    b. **Gmail-Password**: Our app does not collect or store your Gmail password. We only use Gmail for authentication purposes, and your login credentials are securely handled by Google's authentication services.

    c. **OTP (One-Time Password)**: In case you choose to authenticate using OTP, we may collect your phone number to send you the one-time password. We do not store this phone number beyond the authentication process.

    d. **Google Login**: When you log in to our app using Google, we may collect your basic profile information such as your name, email address, and profile picture. Similar to Facebook login, additional information may be collected based on your Google privacy settings.

2. **Use of Information**

    a. We use the information collected to provide and improve our services, personalize your experience, and communicate with you.

    b. Your information may be used to create and maintain your account, provide customer support, and send you important notices regarding the app or your account.

    c. We may also use your information for research and analytics purposes to understand user behavior and improve our services.

3. **Information Sharing**

    a. We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personal information to third parties without your consent, except as described in this policy.

    b. We may share your information with service providers who assist us in operating our app, conducting our business, or serving you. These service providers are obligated to keep your information confidential.

    c. We may also disclose your information when required by law or to protect our rights, property, or safety, or that of others.

4. **Data Security**

    a. We take reasonable measures to protect the security of your personal information against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.

    b. However, please note that no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

5. **Children's Privacy**

    a. Our app is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian and believe that your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us, and we will take steps to remove such information from our systems.

6. **Changes to This Privacy Policy**

    a. We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with a new effective date. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any updates.

7. **Contact Us**

    a. If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our practices regarding your personal information, please contact us at [contact@email.com].

By using our demo app, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy and agree to its terms and conditions.
